00:39:26.159 --> 00:39:30.170
Another thing to keep in mind,
that we talk now a lot about,

00:39:30.170 --> 00:39:34.179
is single parent families and
what a bad problem this is.

00:39:34.179 --> 00:39:38.550
It turns out that the
prevalence of single parent

00:39:38.550 --> 00:39:41.920
families has always been very
high.

00:39:41.920 --> 00:39:43.922
In the 1700s,
for instance,

00:39:43.922 --> 00:39:46.929
this is a quote from a history
book,

00:39:46.929 --> 00:39:49.427
"One the main
characteristics of European

00:39:49.427 --> 00:39:52.481
urban households in the
eighteenth century was the large

00:39:52.481 --> 00:39:55.090
proportion that were headed by
women."

00:39:55.090 --> 00:39:57.829
In Rheims under the Ancien
Regime,

00:39:57.829 --> 00:39:59.929
in France before the French
Revolution,

00:39:59.929 --> 00:40:06.471
one out of four homes was
headed by a woman and 15% to 25%

00:40:06.471 --> 00:40:12.440
in all the towns for which they
have data on this.

00:40:17.670 --> 00:40:21.943
In the U.S.,
the prevalence--the big divorce

00:40:21.943 --> 00:40:25.920
boom came after the 1950s in
America,

00:40:25.920 --> 00:40:28.902
but it turns out that the
prevalence of single parent

00:40:28.902 --> 00:40:32.117
households at the end of the
twentieth century was almost

00:40:32.117 --> 00:40:34.985
