00:56:49.126 --> 00:56:51.699
effectively as adults and in
many--

00:56:51.699 --> 00:56:56.202
in several of the studies,
they used contraception more

00:56:56.202 --> 00:56:58.369
effectively than adults.
 

00:56:58.369 --> 00:57:03.699
If contraception hadn't come in
at that time,

00:57:03.699 --> 00:57:07.675
you would have seen a
tremendous rise in teen

00:57:07.675 --> 00:57:10.112
pregnancy,
in teen births,

00:57:10.112 --> 00:57:13.230
whereas, in fact,
you saw a gentle,

00:57:13.230 --> 00:57:17.429
a 1% a year,
a gentle drop in teen births.

00:57:22.768 --> 00:57:30.617
Cross-national studies show
quite convincingly that the

00:57:30.617 --> 00:57:34.766
drop--
that the moderation of this

00:57:34.766 --> 00:57:41.181
drop that why teen pregnancy
didn't rise when teen sex rose

00:57:41.181 --> 00:57:44.280
was due to contraception.
 

00:57:44.280 --> 00:57:46.163
In Canada, U.S.,
Sweden, France,

00:57:46.163 --> 00:57:48.896
Great Britain,
the age of sexual debut doesn't

00:57:48.896 --> 00:57:52.300
change very much when you go
across these countries.

00:57:52.300 --> 00:57:56.246
About 40% of the 15 to 17 year
olds have already have

00:57:56.246 --> 00:58:00.726
intercourse and this rises to
70% to 80% among 18 to 19 year

00:58:00.726 --> 00:58:01.409
olds.
 

00:58:01.409 --> 00:58:02.630
In fact, the U.S.
 

00:58:02.630 --> 00:58:06.364
